body:
Can we do away with all this MakeUniqueBuffer fanciness and instead have:

```
TF_Buffer* crun_options = nullptr;
// ...
if (crun_options != nullptr) TF_DeleteBuffer(crun_options);
```

Since there is only one place where we create the TF_Buffer and only one path to the point where it can be deleted, just like all other cleanup functions?

